&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_x_MsoNormal&quot; data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Xebia is a global AI-first, digital transformation, and engineering partner.&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;With over 25 years of experience and a team of 5,000 professionals across 16 countries, we help organizations design and build scalable products, platforms, and data-driven solutions.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;We specialize in Artificial Intelligence, Data and Cloud, Intelligent Automation, and Digital Products, combining deep technical expertise with a strong focus on engineering excellence and a people-first culture.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&gt;In the CEE region, we’re a team of nearly 1,000 experts delivering modern applications, data platforms, and AI solutions for clients such as McLaren, Aviva, Deloitte, Spotify, Disney, ING, UPS, Tesco, Truecaller, AllSaints, Volotea, Schmitz Cargobull, Allegro, InPost, and many, many more. We work with leading technologies including AWS, Azure, GCP, Databricks, and Snowflake, and combine strong engineering culture with a consulting mindset and a continuous focus on growth and knowledge sharing.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The project focuses on augmenting business and data analysts using AI agents built on top of the Databricks ecosystem. The goal is to accelerate insight generation, reduce manual analytical effort, and improve decision-making quality across Operations, Finance, and Digital domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;leading discovery workshops to define what “analyst augmentation” means in practical, measurable terms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;identifying and prioritizing high-value analyst workflows (OPS, Finance, Digital),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;defining success metrics such as analyst time reduction, query accuracy, and turnaround time,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;auditing existing Databricks data assets, pipelines, and governance constraints,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;preparing AI-ready datasets, including metadata, documentation, and semantic layers,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;designing and prototyping AI agents that replicate or support analyst tasks,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;implementing agents using Databricks tools (e.g., Genie, Unity Catalog),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;defining and implementing guardrails (security, cost control, hallucination prevention),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;evaluating AI agent performance against human analyst benchmarks,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;supporting pilot deployment to a limited group of business users,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;measuring business impact and contributing to ROI and scaling recommendations,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;helping define the roadmap from proof-of-concept to production deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your profile:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;strong experience in data analytics, data engineering, or analytics platform delivery,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;hands-on experience with Databricks (including Unity Catalog and governed data access),&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience working with SQL and analytical data models,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;solid understanding of data governance, security, and access control concepts,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience designing or working with AI/LLM-based solutions in an analytics context,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ability to translate business workflows into technical and AI-enabled solutions,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;strong stakeholder commu

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hello, let’s meet!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While Xebia is a global tech company, our journey in CEE started with two Polish companies – PGS Software, known for world-class cloud and software solutions, and GetInData, a pioneer in Big Data. Today, we’re a team of 1,000+ experts delivering top-notch work across cloud, data, and software. And we’re just getting started.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work on projects that matter – and that make a difference. From fintech and e-commerce to aviation, logistics, media, and fashion, we help our clients build scalable platforms, data and AI solutions, and cutting-edge applications to shape the future of tech. Our clients include McLaren, Aviva, Deloitte, Spotify, Disney, ING, UPS, Tesco, Truecaller, AllSaints, Volotea, Schmitz Cargobull, Allegro, InPost, and many, many more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value smart tech, real ownership, and continuous growth. We use modern, open-source stacks, and we’re proud to be trusted partners of Databricks, dbt, Snowflake, Azure, GCP, and AWS. Fun fact: we were the first AWS Premier Partner in Poland!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beyond Projects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What makes Xebia special? Our community. We support tech communities, organize meetups (Software Talks, Data Tech Talks), and have a culture that actively support your growth via Guilds, Labs, and personal development budgets — for both tech and soft skills. It’s not just a job. It’s a place to grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What sets us apart?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our mindset. Our vibe. Our people. And while that’s hard to capture in text – come visit us and see for yourself.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;designing, building, and maintaining cloud-native AI platforms and infrastructure,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;developing, deploying, and optimising AI agent solutions using modern agentic frameworks, MCP, and AI runtime technologies,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;enabling engineering teams through AI-assisted development, automation, and developer productivity tools,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;collaborating with software engineers, AI specialists, and platform teams to deliver scalable, secure, and production-ready AI solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your profile:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience as a DevOps Engineer, Platform Engineer, or Cloud Engineer on&amp;nbsp;AWS, Azure, or GCP,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;hands-on experience with AI-assisted development tools such as Claude, Kiro, GitHub Copilot, or workflow automation platforms like n8n,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;practical experience designing, building, and deploying AI agents and agent-based workflows,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience with agentic runtimes, including xAgentic Runtime or similar frameworks,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;working knowledge of FastMCP, LangGraph, Model Context Protocol (MCP), and modern AI Agent Architectures,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience applying AI-assisted development practices to improve software delivery, automation, and developer productivity,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;strong understanding of Infrastructure as Code, CI/CD, containerization, and cloud-native technologies,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently in a fast-paced environment,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;strong communication skills,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;fluent English (at least B2 level).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
